    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-05-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-05-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="523" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d523">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">White</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">St.
                                    Petersburg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-05-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 19, 1893</hi>
                        </date>.
                            (Received June 1.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 97.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my No. 22 and previous dispatches
                        relating to Jacob Goldstein, I have the honor to state that a letter from
                        Mr. Consul Heenan, at Odessa, informs me that the local court at Kharkoff
                        has decided in Goldstein’s favor, but that he “took French leave” last
                        December, has not been since heard of, and that his present whereabouts are
                        unknown,</p>
                <p>I am, sir, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Andrew D. White.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
